    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\nHere's what I found from exploring the codebase and the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n### What I studied\n\n- **`packages/next/server.js`** — verbose CJS pattern: build an exports object, assign `module.exports`, then repeat each as `exports.X` for named ESM imports\n- **`packages/next/server.d.ts`** — named `export { X } from 'next/dist/...'` declarations (not `export *`)\n- **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/user-agent.ts`** — pure functions, no external deps, two variants: `userAgentFromString(rawString)` and `userAgent({ headers })`\n- **`packages/next/package.json`** — no `exports` field; `files` array is the only thing to update; `\"geo.js\"/\"geo.d.ts\"` inserts alphabetically after `\"form.d.ts\"`\n\n---\n\n### 5 Files to change\n\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| CREATE | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| CREATE | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n| CREATE | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| CREATE | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| MODIFY | `packages/next/package.json` (+2 lines) |\n\n---\n\n### Key implementation decisions\n\n- **`geo.ts`**: Pure TypeScript, zero external imports. `geoFromHeaders(headers)` reads `x-vercel-ip-*` headers with `cf-ipcountry` as Cloudflare fallback; `?? undefined` converts `null` from `Headers.get()` to `undefined` for strict-mode compliance. `geo({ headers })` wraps it (mirrors `userAgent` → `userAgentFromString`). Haversine formula uses Earth radius 6371 km.\n- **`geo.js`**: Follows `server.js` pattern exactly (build object + `module.exports` + named `exports.X`)\n- **`geo.d.ts`**: Named `export { X }` and `export type { Geo }` from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n- **`package.json`**: Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` — no `exports` field to update\n- **`geo.test.ts`**: `import assert from 'node:assert'` only; tests Vercel headers, Cloudflare fallback, priority logic, empty headers, all 10 country lookups, `isInRegion` case-insensitivity, and Haversine NYC→London ≈ 5570 km ±50 km",
